<br>
If your time frame doesn't conform to your speculation on VS spawn time, then maybe a transfer to a server based in another time frame (i.e. Europe) would be beneficial to you.<br>
<br>
I am a 61 wizard on Rodcet Nife.  I don't sit around in PoT LFG.  I'll /ooc in the zone and over guild then I'll head to Skyfire or other zones and quad.  At 61, the exp earned per kill is pretty much the same as level 59, but the mobs are more scarce.  You just have to go to various places and find a spot that works for your level of skill, whether that is expedition guards in GD, elder wyverns in Skyfire, or flies in PoD.<br>
<br>
In regards to my use of skin buffs, it really depends upon where I am quadding or if I am in a group how well the MT maintains aggro.  When quadding, I generally have 3 buffs on me (shield of the arcane, kei, familiar) and the occasional skin spell.  If I had my epic, then yes, I would have it up all the time.<br>
<br>
Also, you play at a great time to do bazaar shopping.  You can turn a lot of plat real fast by finding pricing errors and undercutting then turning it around and selling at market value. Instead of wasting hundreds of hours in KC, just play the market, make the plat, then buy the MQ for the staff.  On RN, the MQ's can be bought for 5-10k (some times cheaper). All you would need is one of the staffs, then buy the other two, complete your epic and there you have your missing level 60 skin spell.<br>
<br>
One thing perplexes me though, you accuse others of spamming you with their responses to your question.  You argue that opinion is spam.  Does that mean the premise of this thread is spam because it is your opinion that a level 60 skin spell is missing?<br>
<br>
Hannabel Voltaire<br>
Rodcet Nife<br>
