<br>
So yeah, sometimes spell lines or abilities get dropped.  On the other hand, sometimes new abilities get unlocked.  Remember how from 1 to 49, every single new nuke took longer and longer to cast?  I doubt anyone would argue that draughts are a welcome break from that trend.  In the post-60 game, enchanters got their first componentless rune.  Why?  Because of the changing balance of the game at those levels. <p>Bayler - Marauder/Deceiver - Xev<br>
